

WWW::Quvi
============

WWW::Quvi are the Perl bindings for libquvi.

This module provides a Perl interface to libquvi. This documentation
contains the Perl specific details and some sample code. The libquvi
documentation should be consulted for the API details at
<http://quvi.googlecode.com/>.

WWW: <http://www-quvi.googlecode.com/>
GIT: <git://repo.or.cz/www-quvi.git>


PREREQUISITES

  * quvi 0.2.5+  <http://quvi.googlecode.com/>
    - 0.2.0 should be OK, though some WWW::Quvi tests (e.g. version) *will* fail

  * Perl 5.8.9+  <http://perl.org/>

Additionally (to build):
  * ExtUtils::MakeMaker <http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?ExtUtils::Depends>
  * ExtUtils::PkgConfig <http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?ExtUtils::PkgConfig>
  * ExtUtils::Depends   <http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?ExtUtils::Depends>


INSTALLATION

To install this module, type the following:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test (optional, see notes below)
    make install (see notes below)


WHAT IS NOT IMPLEMENTED

  * Callbacks (e.g. status callback)

  * Multiple download links per video


NOTES

* Developed on and for Linux, should port fairly easily to other systems

* You can edit CXXFLAGS LDFLAGS, etc. in Makefile.PL
    - ExtUtils::MakeMaker supports many more (see the URLs below)

* Set HAVE_INTERNET if you want to run the internet dependant tests

* You can specify an install "prefix" with INSTALL_BASE
    - e.g. perl Makefile.PL INSTALL_BASE=/usr/local

  More: <http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?ExtUtils::MakeMaker>
   FAQ: <http://perldoc.perl.org/ExtUtils/MakeMaker/FAQ.html>


